      "content": {
        "title": "Acquisition, Extinction, and Spontaneous Recovery",
        "definition": "Strengthening of CS–US associations, their weakening when US is omitted, and return over time.",
        "summary": "Extinction is new inhibitory learning, not erasure of original memory."
      },
